bug.short_desc: Overflow scrollbar of splitpane in front of qx.ui.window.Window

long_desc.thetext: I am using a split frame. Then I am opening a qx.ui.window.Window. The left pane of my split shows an overflow scrollbar. If I am moving the window over that area the scrollbar should be behind the window but it is not.
That's a bug in Firefox (or rather the Gecko engine in general) on Mac OS X. I don't know of any workarounds that could be employed in qooxdoo.

There is a proposed solution for this problem: http://www.errorforum.com/mozilla-firefox-error/3503-will-float-mac-firefox-scrollbars-floating-pop-up-windows.html
We may have to check if this could be applied to qooxdoo as well.
This is the original Mozilla bug: https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=187435

Setting the overflow value of qx.ui.popup.Popup and it's subclasses to "auto" forces the scrollbar to render in the background. Unfortunately the borders are still overwritten by the scrollbars.
The complete solution is probably overkill for qooxdoo as a framework.
In the current svn overflow = "auto" is now the default for all Popups including tooltips, menus and windows.

I suggest to remove the overflow:auto fix again as it breaks internal windows (even in Firefox on a Mac). A screenshot is attached. Without overflow:auto, all looks good again (except for the original scrollbar bug of course, but I don't think it's qooxdoo's job to fix that).
If no one objects, I'll remove the fix within the next few days.
